.TH GILDERD 1 "2026-06-18" "Gilder" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gilderd \- Wayland wallpaper daemon for Gilder
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gilderd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gilderd
is the user-session daemon for Gilder. It owns the local Unix socket, reads the
Gilder configuration and persisted state, watches desktop output state through
configured adapters, and dispatches wallpaper render plans to enabled renderers.
.PP
The daemon binds
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/gilder/gilder.sock
and only accepts local user-session IPC. It is intended to run as a systemd user
service or as a compositor autostart command.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gilder/config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I $XDG_STATE_HOME/gilder/state.json
Persisted wallpaper state.
.TP
.I $XDG_CACHE_HOME/gilder/
Render cache and unpacked wallpaper archives.
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/gilder/gilder.sock
IPC socket.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B GILDER_POWER_STATE
Validation override for the daemon power state. Accepted values are
.BR ac ,
.BR battery ,
and
.BR unknown .
When unset, Gilder reads power state from sysfs.
.TP
.B GILDER_OUTPUT_STATE
Validation override for output desktop state. Accepted values are
.BR active ,
.BR unfocused ,
.BR fullscreen ,
and
.BR hidden .
When unset, Gilder uses compositor or GDK output state.
.TP
.B GILDER_SESSION_STATE
Validation override for logind session state. Accepted values are
.BR active ,
.BR inactive ,
and
.BR locked .
When unset, Gilder reads session active and locked hints from logind when
available.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gilderctl (1),
.BR gilder-convert (1)
